setExtrusion

public void setExtrusion(double speed,
                         boolean rev)
                  throws java.io.IOException,
                         java.lang.Exception
Start the extruder motor at a given speed. In the old scheme, this ranges from 0 to 255 but is scaled by maxSpeed and t0, so that 255 corresponds to the highest permitted speed. It is also scaled so that 0 would correspond with the lowest extrusion speed. In the new scheme speed is simply mm/sec.

Specified by:
setExtrusion in interface org.reprap.Extruder
Parameters:
speed - The speed to drive the motor at (0-255)
rev - If set, run extruder in reverse
Throws:
java.io.IOException
java.lang.Exception

getAngleSpeedFactor

public double getAngleSpeedFactor()
The factor by which to speed up when going round a corner. The formula is speed = baseSpeed*[1 - 0.5*(1 + ca)*getAngleSpeedFactor()] where ca is the cos of the angle between the lines. So it goes fastest when the line doubles back on itself (returning 1), and slowest when it continues straight (returning 1 - getAngleSpeedFactor()). (non-Javadoc)

Specified by:
getAngleSpeedFactor in interface org.reprap.Extruder
Returns:
the angle-speed factor
See Also:
Extruder.getAngleSpeedFactor()
